BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:b4H3DgmrSL0AESdqNnh-G
SUMMARY:Ain't Misbehavin'
DTSTAMP:20260410T044129Z
DTSTART:20260411T023000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Fats Waller Music Show by Richard Maltby Jr.\n\nThe Fats Wa
	ller Musical Show The club is alive\, the band is swingin’\, and the music
	 of a jazz legend brings the house down. This immersive musical revue cele
	brates the life of Fats Waller on stage with joy\, rhythm\, and soul. Reme
	mbering his generation-defining songs and lasting impact on today’s music\
	, this exuberant Tony Award-winning tribute to Black artistry sings\, laug
	hs\, hopes\, and lives out loud.\n\nhttps://web.ovationtix.com/trs/pe.c/37
	019\n\nFrom Taproot Theatre
URL:https://web.ovationtix.com/trs/pe.c/37019
LOCATION:Taproot Theatre\, 204 N 85th St\, Seattle\, WA 98103
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:taproot
CATEGORIES:Taproot Theatre
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TWS42QY66gwjRf6RjW_SC
SUMMARY:CPR\\\, First Aid & HIV Certification
DTSTAMP:20260410T044129Z
DTSTART:20260411T090000Z
DESCRIPTION:Learn first aid\\\, infant\\\, child and adult CPR\\\, HIV and 
	bloodborne pathogens\\\, with a focus on injury prevention and safety. Mee
	ts L/I WISHA-WAC safety standards. Certificates issued at end of class. \\
	nCan you provide first aid in emergencies\\\, locate and take care of inju
	ries\\\, help a choking infant or child and stop cardiac arrest? Learn fir
	st aid\\\, infant\\\, child and adult CPR\\\, HIV and bloodborne pathogens
	\\\, with a focus on injury prevention and safety. \\nModified to meet COV
	ID-19 safety requirements (hands-on only\\\, no mouth-to mouth). \\nMeets 
	L/I WISHA-WAC safety standards. Certificates issued at end of class. \\nTa
	ught by Ken Norris\\\, Retired Firefighter. \\nLocation: Upper Blue Buildi
	ng\\\, Room 7.\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/cpr-first-aid-hiv-ce
	rtification-2026-04/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/cpr-first-aid-hiv-certification-202
	6-04/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\
	\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:YezfPfLhhxr3ydKuECIa_
SUMMARY:PNA Woodshop\\\, dedicated to Bill Fenimore
DTSTAMP:20260410T044129Z
DTSTART:20260411T093000Z
DESCRIPTION:Did you know that there is a woodshop in your area? Whether you
	’re a newcomer to woodworking or an experienced woodworker\\\, the PNA woo
	dshop is the ideal place to bring your creative projects to life. Whether 
	you’re interested in crafting a bench\\\, flower bed\\\, jewelry box\\\, c
	hair\\\, or cupboard\\\, the possibilities are endless. All you need to do
	 is become a PNA member\\\, attend an orientation\\\, and complete two saf
	ety classes. Once you’ve done that\\\, you can reserve your shop time and 
	get started on your project.\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/pna-wo
	odshop-dedicated-to-bill-fenimore/2026-04-11/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborhood
	 Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/pna-woodshop-dedicated-to-bill-feni
	more/2026-04-11/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave
	. N.\\\, Seattle\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:UHNjpAKgy-DvZiNE0sLGC
SUMMARY:The Canote Brothers in Concert
DTSTAMP:20260410T044129Z
DTSTART:20260411T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Jere and Greg Canote are identical twins from Seattle\\\, WA wh
	o perform as the Canote Brothers. They are known nationally through their 
	touring and teaching at music camps and festivals across the country. The 
	brothers have played an important role in the old-time music scene on the 
	West Coast through a string band class they have been teaching for several
	 decades\\\, and they are known for their infectious\\\, positive energy\\
	\, and for humorously capitalizing on their relationship as identical twin
	s. \\nThey specialize in old time fiddle tunes\\\, saying “We love the hyp
	notic ‘in the moment’ experience of playing this American Old Time music.”
	 From the synopsis of the recent documentary about them: “Anyone close eno
	ugh to be caught up in this vortex of joy\\\, is likely to end up feeling 
	happier and more optimistic about themselves and the world!” \\nDoors open
	 at 7 pm for the 7:30 pm concert in the Phinney Center’s Community Hall (l
	ower Brick Building). \\nTickets available online or at prior Seattle Folk
	lore Society concerts\\\, or at the door (subject to availability).\n\nhtt
	ps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/the-canote-brothers-in-concert/\n\nFrom P
	hinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/the-canote-brothers-in-concert/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave
	. N.\\\, Seattle\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
